\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces Population-averaged survival $S(t)$ under MAR and MNAR assumptions. Transparent curves show 200 posterior draws per model; bold lines show posterior means. The MAR draws (grey) and Kaplan--Meier (dashed black) closely track through day~10. Colored draw-clouds show MNAR-adjusted survival under $\sigma _\gamma \in \{0.5, 1.0, 2.0\}$. Wider priors produce both larger shifts and wider posterior spread.}}{9}{figure.caption.3}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:survival}{{3}{9}{Population-averaged survival $S(t)$ under MAR and MNAR assumptions. Transparent curves show 200 posterior draws per model; bold lines show posterior means. The MAR draws (grey) and Kaplan--Meier (dashed black) closely track through day~10. Colored draw-clouds show MNAR-adjusted survival under $\sigma _\gamma \in \{0.5, 1.0, 2.0\}$. Wider priors produce both larger shifts and wider posterior spread}{figure.caption.3}{}}
